{
  "texts": [
    "Philosophers like John Rawls and Amartya Sen offer principles to evaluate AI ethics and policy.",
    "Rawls' theory of justice as fairness emphasizes equitable distribution of social goods and opportunities.",
    "Two key Rawlsian ideas apply to AI ethics: fair equality of opportunity and the difference principle.",
    "Fair opportunity means positions and services (like AI-driven benefits) should be open to all under conditions of equality, which in AI translates to non-discrimination by algorithms and equal access to AI tools.",
    "The difference principle holds that inequalities are acceptable only if they benefit the least advantaged members of society (Westerstrand 2024)."
  ]
}